  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-05 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). This package contains a subtle W-AR-05 weakness: one validation result omits the comparedAgainst link, and the comparator used elsewhere derives from ventricular assist device (VAD) bench tests rather than CPB operating conditions.",
